725905f-a.title: Queens: 150th Street - South Road
725905f-a.text:
150th Street (Rockaway Turnpike), north from South Road (tracks
thereon), showing at the corner a peaked roof house, in which, John
Fitrgerald kept a saloon. A three story brick building occupied the
site in 1931.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
